# Astro Component Patterns

## Frontmatter
Keep the `---` fence clean: imports at the top, then data fetching, then derived values.

```astro
---
// ✅ GOOD — ordered, typed
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { getCollection } from "astro:content";

const posts = await getCollection("blog");
const sorted = posts.sort((a, b) => b.data.date.getTime() - a.data.date.getTime());
---
```

## Props
Always type component props explicitly:

```astro
---
// ✅ GOOD
interface Props {
  title: string;
  description?: string;
}
const { title, description = "" } = Astro.props;
---

---
// ❌ BAD — untyped
const { title, description } = Astro.props;
---
```

## Page vs Component vs Layout
- **Pages** live in `src/pages/` and export a full HTML shell via a Layout
- **Layouts** live in `src/layouts/` and use `<slot />`
- **Components** live in `src/components/` and are purely presentational

## Dynamic Routes
Use `getStaticPaths()` for `[slug].astro` pages. Always destructure from `Astro.params`.

```astro
---
export async function getStaticPaths() {
  const entries = await getCollection("blog");
  return entries.map((entry) => ({ params: { slug: entry.id } }));
}
const { slug } = Astro.params;
---
```

## Links
Always use trailing slashes on internal links: `/projects/${id}/` not `/projects/${id}`.
